<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="535" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/432</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Netherland Chargé</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">De Beaufort</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-04">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 4, 1918</hi>.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to accept the recent
                                proposition of the United States Government concerning the three
                                ships which will leave [for] the Netherlands loaded with grain.</p>
                            <p>This proposition is understood by my Government as follows:</p>
                            <p>The Netherland ships <hi rend="italic">Java, Stella</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Hollandia</hi> will leave for the Netherlands
                                loaded with grain, upon three ships of equivalent tonnage leaving
                                the Netherlands, of which two will proceed to United States ports
                                and one to Buenos Aires. The three last-mentioned ships will upon
                                their arrival be enabled to load grain of the amount which has been
                                placed at the disposal of the Netherland Government and they will
                                receive all the facilities for their return to the Netherlands upon
                                the <hi rend="italic">Java, Stella</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Hollandia</hi> or equivalent tonnage returning from the
                                Netherlands.</p>
                            <p>Please accept [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DBWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. de Beaufort</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>